definition: Iron-Crutch Li, one of the Eight Immortals 八仙[Ba1 xian1] in Chinese mythology, walking around with an iron crutch and carrying a gourd with special medicine

sentences.english: Mr. Li Tieying, new President of Toy Shan Association, extended his holiday greetings to the guests.
sentences.chinese: 台山同鄉會新任會長李鐵英向來賓致以新春問候。

sentences.english: James is also the director and advisor of several private equity funds.
sentences.chinese: 李鐵也是多家基金的董事及參與人。

sentences.english: Bittersweet laugh instead of salty language, and then later at dusk, and Li Xiao also arrived.
sentences.chinese: 酸甜苦辣鹹笑而不語，再後來黃昏曉和李鐵也來了。

sentences.english: Li Tie is a really powerful writer of the "new generation".
sentences.chinese: 李鐵屬於“新生代”實力派作家。

sentences.english: Tie a Starting Knot as shown, then hold the laces as pictured.
sentences.chinese: 李鐵開始結所示，然後按住花邊的照片。

sentences.english: Li Tie and Snu Jihai are Chinese international football players.
sentences.chinese: 李鐵和孫繼海使中國的國際足球運動員。
